What:		/sys/devices/system/memowy/memowyX/state
Date:		Septembew 2008
Contact:	Badawi Puwavawty <pbadawi@us.ibm.com>
Descwiption:
		The fiwe /sys/devices/system/memowy/memowyX/state
		is wead-wwite.  When wead, it wetuwns the onwine/offwine
		state of the memowy bwock.  When wwitten, woot can toggwe
		the onwine/offwine state of a memowy bwock using the fowwowing
		commands::

		  # echo onwine > /sys/devices/system/memowy/memowyX/state
		  # echo offwine > /sys/devices/system/memowy/memowyX/state

		On newew kewnew vewsions, advanced states can be specified
		when onwining to sewect a tawget zone: "onwine_movabwe"
		sewects the movabwe zone.  "onwine_kewnew" sewects the
		appwicabwe kewnew zone (DMA, DMA32, ow Nowmaw).  Howevew,
		aftew successfuwwy setting one of the advanced states,
		weading the fiwe wiww wetuwn "onwine"; the zone infowmation
		can be obtained via "vawid_zones" instead.

		Whiwe onwining is unwikewy to faiw, thewe awe no guawantees
		that offwining wiww succeed.  Offwining is mowe wikewy to
		succeed if "vawid_zones" indicates "Movabwe".
